{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"43c5b0d2-f9ef-417c-b0fa-cc87edb3d7fb","content":"PID 12345 isn't running on this machine, so I can't inspect it directly. Here's how to determine the runtime and configure dumps on your target system:\n\n## 1. Identify the Runtime\n\n```bash\n# CoreCLR loads libcoreclr.so; NativeAOT does not\ncat /proc/12345/maps | grep -i libcoreclr\n```\n\n- **Match found** → **CoreCLR**\n- **No match** → likely **NativeAOT** (confirm: the binary is a self-contained single file with no `*.dll` alongside it, and `file /proc/12345/exe` shows a statically-linked ELF)\n\n## 2. Configure Crash Dumps\n\n### For CoreCLR\n\nSet these environment variables **before** launching the app (e.g. in your systemd unit or shell):\n\n```bash\n# Enable full crash dumps\nexport DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1\nexport DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType=4          # 4 = Full (Triage=1, Mini=2, Heap=3)\nexport DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName=/tmp/dumps/coredump.%p.%t\nmkdir -p /tmp/dumps\n```\n\nAlso ensure the OS core-dump limit is sufficient:\n\n```bash\nulimit -c unlimited\n```\n\n### For NativeAOT\n\nNativeAOT does **not** use the `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump` variables. It relies on the **OS core dump mechanism**:\n\n```bash\n# 1. Remove core size limit\nulimit -c unlimited\n\n# 2. Configure the kernel core pattern\nsudo sysctl -w kernel.core_pattern=/tmp/dumps/core.%e.%p.%t\nsudo mkdir -p /tmp/dumps\n```\n\nIf your distro routes dumps through `systemd-coredump` (check with `cat /proc/sys/kernel/core_pattern`), dumps land in `/var/lib/systemd/coredump/` and you retrieve them with `coredumpctl`.\n\n## 3. Analyze Dumps\n\n| Runtime | Tool |\n|-----------|------|\n| CoreCLR | `dotnet-dump analyze <dump>` or `lldb` with SOS (`dotnet-sos install`) |\n| NativeAOT | `gdb` or `lldb` (standard native debugging; no SOS/DAC) |\n\n**Quick check you can run right now** on your target host:\n\n```bash\nif grep -q libcoreclr /proc/12345/maps 2>/dev/null; then\n  echo \"CoreCLR — use DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump\"\nelse\n  echo \"NativeAOT — use kernel core_pattern\"\nfi\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6e5704b9-9e7d-4d0d-94de-2277bf494da3","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The process doesn't exist on this machine (PID 12345). That makes sense — the user is asking for guidance, not expecting me to inspect a live process on this machine. Let me provide them with a comprehensive guide on how to determine the runtime and configure dumps.","outputTokens":744,"requestId":"6404:C174F:1519826:18A1B2D:69EC1AC6"},"id":"09bd869b-6c20-4d9a-b476-571ce097078a","timestamp":"2026-04-25T01:37:27.537Z","parentId":"bb18e2ca-5c4f-4c4e-bc0e-3a3af0862c0d"}
